{
  "texts": [
    "P3.2: inadequate metric aggregation.",
    "A common pitfall with respect to metric application is to simply aggregate metric values over the entire dataset and/or all classes.",
    "As detailed in Figure 6b and Supplementary Note 2.3.2, important information can be lost in this process, and metric results can be misleading.",
    "For example, the popular Torch-Metrics framework calculates the DSC metric by default as a global average over all pixels in the dataset without considering their image or class of origin (https://torchmetrics.readthedocs.io/en/stable/ classification/dice.html?highlight=dice).",
    "Such a calculation eliminates the possibility of interpreting the final metric score with respect to individual images and classes."
  ]
}